<P ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT SIZE="-1" COLOR="GREEN"><I>Rig Veda</I>, tr. by Ralph T.H. Griffith, [1896], at sacred-texts.com</FONT></P><HR></p>  <h3 align="center" align="center">HYMN CL. Agni.</h3>  
<p>1. AGNI, thy faithful servant I call upon thee with many a gift,<br> As in the keeping of the great inciting God;<br> 2 Thou who ne&#146;er movest thee to aid the indolent, the godless man,<br> Him who though wealthy never brings an offering.<br> 3 Splendid, O Singer, is that man, mightiest of the great in heaven.<br> Agni, may we be foremost, we thy worshippers.</p>  
